# Git Conflict Safety

- Never reformat unrelated files.
- Never reorder unrelated imports.
- Never rename existing symbols without instruction.
- Never move or delete files without instruction.
- Never modify package files unless required.
- Never modify global routing for a module-local task unless explicitly asked.
- Never modify shared files for convenience.
- Keep changes inside the assigned module.
- Before editing, list the files that will be changed.
- Use the smallest possible diff.
- If a change requires touching another owner's module, stop and explain the dependency.
